## 🔵 Searching Inside Files

| Command | What it Does | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `grep 'word' file` | Find lines containing a word | `grep 'millionth' data.txt` |
| `grep -i 'word' file` | Case insensitive search | `grep -i 'password' data.txt` |
| `grep -n 'word' file` | Show line numbers of matches | `grep -n 'millionth' data.txt` |
| `grep -v 'word' file` | Show lines NOT containing word | `grep -v 'false' data.txt` |
| `grep -r 'word' .` | Search recursively in all files | `grep -r 'password' .` |
| `grep -w 'word' file` | Returns only the word not the entire line | `grep -w 'millionth' data.txt` |

